description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONTINUING HEALTH CARE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NURSE ASSESSOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week (1.0 wte )&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part-time / full-time / job share welcome &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Welcome to Your Healthcare CIC, formerly part of NHS Kingston we are a not for profit social enterprise, proud of delivering patient-led, high quality health and social care community services for residents in Kingston &amp; Richmond as part of the NHS family.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your Healthcare is located in the South West of London within the Royal Borough of Kingston. Working as a Community Interest Company (CIC), our status allows us to invest any surplus or profit back into front line services, where it is needed most by you, our community. Our organisation offers access to the NHS pension scheme, staff discounts, Agenda for Change terms and conditions.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The CHC assessing team are commissioned by Kingston &amp; Richmond CCG, part of the SW London Alliance to deliver the continuing health care assessments in line with the department of Health guidelines to residents of the Royal Borough of Kingston, registered with a Kingston GP. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an experienced Band 6 Continuing Health care (CHC) nurse assessor to join our small, friendly CHC team. The CHC team is based at Hollyfield House, Hollyfield Road, Surbiton.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The CHC team visit elderly, frail &amp; vulnerable people in their own or care &amp; nursing homes so clear concise oral &amp; written communication is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We work with &amp; liaise with the wider integrated community provision offered by Your Healthcare and our fellow service providers&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a continually evolving service we have re-designed our current provision around the national guidelines for Covid 19 we currently offer virtual reviews &amp; assessments within that new framework. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant would be enthusiastic and have at least 2 years CHC assessing experience with a knowledge of The National Framework &amp; it’s application across all aspects of CHC work. Our CHC team has an excellent mix of skills and experience so as part of the team and the wider Your Healthcare services the post holder will receive high quality supervision and support for further development. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As we are a community service the post holder will need to have a full, valid driving licence and be able to travel between places of work. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The organisation offers:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Access to the NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Career Development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Staff Discounts&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to contact us to discuss any aspects of this role please contact: Lynn Herridge, CHC Clinical Team Lead.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tel: 0208 274 7065&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;lynn.herridge@yourhealthcare.org&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Due to the post holder having access to vulnerable adults, the successful candidate will be required to undertake an Enhanced DBS check.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your Healthcare CIC reserves the right to close this vacancy prior to the advertised closing date if a high number of applications are received. If you are interested in this role, please submit your application as soon as possible.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are successful at interview, please note we will take up references covering your last 3 years’ work history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLOSING DATE:19th November2020 &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTERVIEWS: TBC&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;JOB SHARE APPLICANTS WELCOME WITH OR WITHOUT A PARTNER&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your Healthcare is an equal opportunities employer and positively encourages applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of sex, race, disability, age, sexual orientation, gender reassignment, religion or belief, marital status, or pregnancy and maternity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
